  "text": "Beyond these points of collective disagreement with Factor One, the remaining positions remained unique in character across both studies. Each expressed a different, nuanced perspective of caution and scepticism towards the use of markets in conservation. Sandbrook et al. defined the ICCB study's Factor Two as having \"ideological scepticism of the underlying rationale for market-based conservation\" [CITATION_1] ). Details of Factors Two and Three in the Cambridge study are given below.",
